{
  "stem": "10549.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He had a radio and listen to it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was-- he liked music.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And one day, early in the morning, I went in front of the prison, and I knew that one of those windows were facing the street.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I couldn't holler in order for him to, to, to see me, but I whistled his favorite tune.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And was very quiet.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he came over to the window.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I had a chance to, to, to say a few words to him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And fortunately, after two weeks later, they released him from the prison.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we lived in Cracow for few months until every, all the Jews had to go to, go to ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they, they made all the Jewish population-- all the Jewish people had to go to Jewish ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Cracow ghetto.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Cracow ghetto.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very cramped, very cramped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can imagine that-- I don't know how many thousands of Jews used to live in a big sections, and all of a sudden the whole ghetto was maybe [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] five or six blocks versus a, a half a city, because Cracow had a big Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a big Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know exactly how many thousands of Jews were there, but there was-- I don't know if it was 50,000 or 70,000.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was very cramped.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't remember how many thousand people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was very cramped conditions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Fortunately, for me and my father that I'm-- on one occasion, where we had to-- it was before we went to ghetto-- we had to register to-- every Jewish person had to register, to go to [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] labor, labor office, like.",
      "word_count": 44
    }
  ],
